INSTALLING POP OS SOMETIMES REMOVES FILES EVEN IF NOT FORMATTED KEEP IN MIND
DOWNLOAD FILES TO EXTERNAL DRIVE AND COPY BACK IN

install pop os:
	format boot partition fat32
	format / root with ext4
	DO NOT FORMAT /xps mount with ext4
	
	startup: choose dock with no edges, clock on right

pop os setup
wifi
authorize core egpu
update everythign in popshop
install golang then follow manual steps for egpu, sudo apt install golang-go
change display, 144hz, 75hz, portrait third monitor
add / and xps to bookmarks, and current uni sem
install tweaks and turn off acceleration, change touchpad right click to area, add maximise button
install chrome, sudo apt purge firefox, make default, turn off telemetry, sign in and sync

for making sure no wifi problems:
	- sudo gedit /etc/modprobe.d/iwlwifi.conf
		- add to bottom "options iwlwifi bt_coex_active=0"
	- sudo gedit /etc/NetworkManager/conf.d/default-wifi-powersave-on.conf 
		- change wifi.powersave  = 2
		

go to gnome extensions:
	- user themes
	- Sound Input & Output Device Chooser 
	- dash to panel:
		- display on all monitors
		- move to top, reduce size to 32
		- move time to centre of monitor
		- unpin useless stuff
	- tiling assistant
	- compiz window effect
		- reduce springiness
	- bluetooth quick connect
	- - arcmenu:
		sudo apt-get install gir1.2-gmenu-3.0
		turn off default applications menu, panel to dock settings -> make applications not 		visible
		change arcmenu settings shortcut to super + space, remove curr shortcut in popshortcuts

add weather to the clock in time

install discord, lutris, vscode, slack, all from popshop
if game is lwo fps, fix dxvk

spotify from chrome

openrazer, polychromatic, sudo gpasswd -a dhruvaa plugdev

settings -> mouse&touchpad -> touchpad natural scrolling

fish: sudo apt install fish
chsh -s `which fish`

change wallpaper/user icon

pipewire:
https://pipewire-debian.github.io/pipewire-debian/

install tela icons

change super + l to lock in shortcuts settings

x11 gestures in gnome extensions:
	- sudo add-apt-repository ppa:touchegg/stable
	
blur my shell gnome extensions


